[src:dotnet-clr/common-intermediate-language] When compiled the methods are stored in tables and the instructions are stored as bytes inside the assembly, which is a Portable Executable (PE).
[src:dotnet-clr/common-intermediate-language] A CIL assembly and instructions are generated by either a compiler or a utility called the *IL Assembler* (ILAsm) that is shipped with the execution environment.
[src:dotnet-clr/common-intermediate-language] Assembled CIL can also be disassembled into code again using the *IL Disassembler* (ILDASM).
